cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a solution that employs supervised neural networks to produce the values of the uncovered locations.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses a hybrid backpropagation method to accelerate the learning convergence speed to a local minimum solution.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with monitoring a region of interest using a set of nodes, which can be seen as a control problem.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with the problem of monitoring a region of interest using a set of nodes, which can be seen as a data structure problem.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper mentions the traditional method of using mobile robots to move around the RoI to collect readings.
